From: kandelo wasm32 port <kandelo@local>
Subject: [PATCH] dynapi: disable on wasm32 — no platform branch in SDL_dynapi.c

src/dynapi/SDL_dynapi.c only knows about Windows, Apple, Linux ELF (via
`__attribute__((constructor))`), HAIKU and a few other platforms. On
wasm32 we have neither of those mechanisms — clang errors with `Please
define your platform.` Defining DYNAPI_NEEDS_DLOPEN via -D won't work:
SDL_config.h sets HAVE_DLOPEN=1 (musl exposes dlopen), so the
NEEDS_DLOPEN branch is bypassed.

Add a `__wasm__` case to SDL_dynapi.h that disables SDL_DYNAMIC_API at
compile time. Dynamic API would be dead weight here anyway — SDL2 is
linked statically into every wasm32 binary; there's no dlopen ABI
contract to preserve.

--- a/src/dynapi/SDL_dynapi.h
+++ b/src/dynapi/SDL_dynapi.h
@@ -68,6 +68,8 @@
 #elif defined(__3DS__)
 #define SDL_DYNAMIC_API 0 /* devkitARM doesn't support dynamic linking */
 #elif defined(DYNAPI_NEEDS_DLOPEN) && !defined(HAVE_DLOPEN)
 #define SDL_DYNAMIC_API 0 /* we need dlopen(), but don't have it.... */
+#elif defined(__wasm__) /* statically linked into each wasm32 binary */
+#define SDL_DYNAMIC_API 0
 #endif

 /* everyone else. This is where we turn on the API if nothing forced it off. */
